
Chapter 8 — System Leakage
Why Your Tech Stack Can Quietly Cost You Revenue

Modern revenue teams have more tools than ever.

CRM.

Marketing Automation.

Sales Engagement.

Customer Success.

AI.

Reporting.

On paper, everything is connected.

In reality, many of these systems barely communicate with each other.

Data gets lost.

Fields don't sync.

Automations fail silently.

Nobody notices until revenue is affected.

This is System Leakage.

What is System Leakage?

System Leakage occurs when disconnected tools, broken integrations, inconsistent data, or poorly designed workflows prevent revenue teams from operating efficiently.

The problem isn't people.

The problem is the system they depend on.

