Real-World Example

A company launches a successful marketing campaign.

Hundreds of leads are generated.

Everything looks normal.

Unknown to the team:

The HubSpot-to-CRM integration failed overnight.
New leads were never assigned.
Sales never received notifications.
Follow-ups never happened.

Marketing believes the campaign performed well.

Sales believes lead quality was poor.

The real problem?

The system failed—not the people.

Revenue Systems Insight

Revenue doesn't just leak through people and processes.

It also leaks through systems that quietly stop doing what they're supposed to do.

The most expensive system failures are usually the ones nobody notices.

Key Takeaways
Modern GTM teams rely on connected systems, not isolated tools.
Data quality is just as important as sales activity.
Silent integration failures create invisible revenue leakage.
RevOps isn't just about optimizing people—it's about designing reliable systems.
AI can continuously audit system health and surface issues before they impact revenue.
